name: Hazel
overview:
Hazel is an American sitcom about a fictional live-in maid named Hazel Burke and her employers, the Baxters. The five-season, 154-episode series aired in primetime from September 28, 1961 until April 11, 1966 and was produced by Screen Gems. The show aired on NBC for its first four seasons, and then on CBS for its final season. The first season, except for one color episode was in black and white, the remainder in color.

The show was based on the popular single-panel comic strip by cartoonist Ted Key, which appeared in the Saturday Evening Post.

episodes.name: Hazel and the Playground
episodes.overview: While trying to teach Harold how to kick a football, Hazel realizes that what is needed in town is a playground for the children.  This leads her to go all out to try to get one despite George and his clients' opinion.

episodes.name: Hazel Makes a Will
episodes.overview: It's that time of the year when Hazel begins warming George up to the idea of a raise but this year, he absolutely refuses, leaving Hazel furious.  Later, when Hazel falls and hurts herself, she decides to draw up a will, but George thinks she's planning a lawsuit against him.

episodes.name: Hazel Plays Nurse
episodes.overview: Hazel plays Nurse for Mr. B & Missy as she taking care of the ill Baxters around the house after getting caught the flu. It's up to Hazel to get them better with a dose of medicine until Harold is the last Baxter to get caught by the flu.

episodes.name: A Matter of Principle
episodes.overview: Hazel is in no mood to be the perfect maid to an important client of George's after she gets a parking ticket that she is sure she didn't deserve.  Although, the fine is only a couple of dollars, Hazel wants George to represent her and help her prove that she wan't at fault.

episodes.name: Dorothy's New Client
episodes.overview: A competitor of Dorothy's is trying to get her to join her interior decorating business but Dorothy is content with her own small business despite few customers.  This prompts Hazel to try to influence the new neighbors into hiring Dorothy to furnish their home.

episodes.name: What'll We Watch Tonight?
episodes.overview: George and Dorothy's nightly television viewing has been getting interupted by Hazel who's excuse is that her television set in her room is broken.  This leads to George taking her down to the store to by her one, which is where she decides to get a color TV and quickly becomes the talk of the town.

episodes.name: A Dog for Harold
episodes.overview: Harold is out playing and finds an abandoned dog and brings him home.  Hazel and Dorothy are overjoyed but the joy becomes fear when they remember that George forbids a dog in the house.  This leads them to plot together to convince George to let Harold keep the dog.

episodes.name: Winter Wonderland
episodes.overview: The Baxters are planning a weekend ski trip to a lodge and Hazel is planning on going along to be in a snow contest with a man she has a crush on.  However, Hazel may have to sit out of the race when George has to work unexpectedly and insists that Hazel stay with him while Harold go along ahead.

episodes.name: Hazel's Winning Personality
episodes.overview: Hazel's friend Laura wants to get the attentions of a new gardner in the neighborhood but has some trouble doing so.  This leads her and Hazel to take a class in changing your personality.  Soon, Hazel begins doing so to hers and begins doing just what the instructor tells the class, shower everyone with compliments.  However, Hazel's constant complimenting gets her into hot water with George and Dorothy.

episodes.name: Hazel's Christmas Shopping
episodes.overview: Hazel has one gift to buy before Christmas and it's for Dorothy.  However, when she discovers she doesn't have enough money for it, she gets a job at a department store and encounters a shoplifter.

episodes.name: Dorothy's Obsession
episodes.overview: Dorothy must have a piano she sees at an antique auction.

episodes.name: The Burglar in Mr. B's P.J.'s
Hazel's Cousin
episodes.overview: Hazel learns that her successful cousin Sybil is going to be married and immediately makes plans to attend the wedding.

episodes.name: We've Been So Happy Till Now
A Four Bit Word to Chew On
Genie With the Light Brown Lamp
I've Been Singing All My Life
The Fires Never Dead While the Ashes Are Red
Hazel Digs a Hole for Herself
An Example for Hazel
episodes.overview: George hopes that Hazel will tone down her brazen ways after meeting his shy spinster cousin.

episodes.name: You Ain't Fully Dressed Without a Smile
episodes.overview: A desk that may or may not have belonged to Abraham Lincoln is given to George as a gift.

episodes.name: Cheerin' Up Mr. B
episodes.overview: Dorothy goes away for a couple days to visit her sister and George gets down in the dumps so Hazel tries to cheer him up.

episodes.name: Hazel Scores a Touchdown
episodes.overview: Fueding football owners become the object of Hazel's obsession, she's determined to bring them together.

episodes.name: George's 32nd Cousin
episodes.overview: George's distant cousin moves in and Hazel quickly becomes sick of her and tries to get her to move out.

episodes.name: All Hazel is Divided Into Three Parts
episodes.overview: Hazel wants to do something to help some poor children so she presents a charity auction.

episodes.name: The Vanishing Hero
episodes.overview: Harold's image of his father is shattered by a visiting athlete's boast that he once 'licked' George when they were children.

episodes.name: Hazel's Nest Egg
episodes.overview: Harold's friend wants to pass the membership test to join the boyscouts so in steps Hazel to help him.

episodes.name: Hazel and the Halfback
episodes.overview: Hazel is putting on a trick bowling exhibition at the bowling alley and tries to get Frank Gifford to attend.

episodes.name: Hot Potato a la Hazel
episodes.overview: The owner of a china shop becomes Hazel's matchmaking victim when she tries to get him and her good friend married.

episodes.name: Scheherezade and Her Frying Pan (1)
episodes.overview: While in Malibu, Hazel and her friend Gracie get mixed up with gangsters.  Gracie's employer is a gangster and a meeting is scheduled at his home which is where Hazel and Gracie become prisoners.

episodes.name: Scheherezade and Her Frying Pan (2)
episodes.overview: Being held prisoner, Hazel and Gracie concoct a plan to get help.  This leads to some close calls as Hazel plans to slip tranquilizers into the gangster's scrambled eggs.

episodes.name: The Fashion Show
episodes.overview: Dorothy is scheduled to appear in a fashion show as a model but when she sprains her ankle, Hazel must take her place.

episodes.name: George's Ordeal
episodes.overview: Hazel makes a bet with Rosie, which puts George in immediate danger, he's got to go on a diet to lose 10 pounds or Hazel loses.

episodes.name: The Reluctant Witness
episodes.overview: Dorothy, an interior decorator, is having problems with her latest customer.  The woman is unhappy with her work and brings a lawsuit against her.

episodes.name: Democracy at Work
episodes.overview: Hazel wants a raise and does her best to try to convince George that she deserves one.

episodes.name: The Countess
episodes.overview: Hazel is in for a shock, she's just inherited the estate of a countess as well as the title.

episodes.name: Hazel's Midas Touch
episodes.overview: George goes all out trying to convince a wealthy socialite to donate his art collection to the art museum.

episodes.name: Everybody's a Comedian
episodes.overview: Hazel adamantly refuses to entertain George's suggestion that she get a pair of glasses.

episodes.name: All Mixed Up
episodes.overview: A new TV commercial for cake mix is being made and a spokewoman is needed to sell it, the director's choice, Hazel.

episodes.name: Arrivederci, Mr. B.
episodes.overview: A non-English speaking Italian girl is trying to keep her baby after her husband goes into the army and his snooty mother-in-law tries to take it from her.  Hazel steps in to offer some aide.

episodes.name: Such a Nice Little Man
episodes.overview: George becomes convinced that the new handyman the Johnsons have hired is a thief.

episodes.name: Campaign Manager
episodes.overview: Hazel tries to convince George that he would be the perfect candidate for city councilman.

episodes.name: Let's Get Away From it All
episodes.overview: The owner of an Italian restaurant needs some extra help since his wife is pregnant, thus Hazel and the Baxters get jobs in the restaurant.

episodes.name: Maid for a Day
episodes.overview: George's sister is cast as a maid in a play and Hazel becomes her coach since being a maid is her profession.

episodes.name: Nerver Trouble Trouble
episodes.overview: The Baxter house has been robbed and the person suspected of doing it is George's cousin, Fred.

episodes.name: Luncheon with the Governor
episodes.overview: The Governor is scheduled to visit the Baxter home for lunch while student protesters decide to stakeout the home awaiting his arrival.

episodes.name: Ain't That a Knee Slapper?
episodes.overview: Harvey Griffin becomes involved in a possible business merger between him and George thanks to Hazel.

episodes.name: Marriage Trap (a.k.a.) George's Law Partner
episodes.overview: George's secretary breaks up with her boyfriend after a big argument and Hazel takes steps to try to bring them back together.

episodes.name: The Flagpole
episodes.overview: George gets a flag as a gift from the Defense Department so Hazel tries to get him to buy a flagpole so he can fly it.

episodes.name: Welcome Back, Kevin
episodes.overview: George's nephew, Kevin and his wife break up after she discovers that he is having an affair, so as usual, Hazel steps in to try to get the two back together.

episodes.name: Mind Your Own Business
episodes.overview: George is fed up with Hazel always snooping in his business and Hazel is fed up with him snooping in hers, they each make a promise to just mind their own business.

episodes.name: High Finance Hits a New Low
episodes.overview: Harriet and Herbert Johnson are having financial problems so George steps in and tries to help.

episodes.name: Just Me, Harold and the Universe
episodes.overview: Hazel enters herself in a contest and becomes a finalist and if she wins she gets a trip for two to the world's fair.

episodes.name: Mix-Up on Marshall Road
episodes.overview: George's partner and his new bride are looking to buy a home so Hazel arranges to sell the neighbor's house so they can have it.

episodes.name: A Lesson in Diplomacy
episodes.overview: A Russian dignitary is staying in the Baxter's home but little do they know that he's really a phony sent there to test them to see if they are the right family to host the real Russian.

episodes.name: To Build or Not to Build
episodes.overview: Hazel wants to have the kitchen remodeled but George is against the idea.  So Hazel comes up with a plan to trick him.

episodes.name: Better to Have Loved and Lost
episodes.overview: George's partner and his wife get into a terrible argument and it's all thanks to Hazel.

episodes.name: Hazel Squares the Triangle
episodes.overview: George's sister, Dierdre and her husband, Harry get into a fight which leads to a break up.  So Hazel tries to get them back together.

episodes.name: Just 86 Shopping Minutes to Christmas
episodes.overview: Dorothy discovers a mink coat in the house and jumps to the conclusion that it's a Christmas gift for her from George.  Little does she know, Harry had bought if for Rita and asked George to hide it for him.

episodes.name: Champagne Tony
episodes.overview: Hazel is all excited because a famous golfer, Tony Lema, is going to be at the airport but once she's their, problems arise.

episodes.name: It's a Dog's Life (a.k.a) It's a Dog's World
episodes.overview: Unwanted houseguests invade the Baxter home and Hazel tries to help the Baxter get rid of them and their untrained dog.

episodes.name: Love 'em and Leave 'em
episodes.overview: Harold has a date to go to the school dance but he also has an escort who's going to accompany him and his date, Hazel.

episodes.name: Temper, Temper
episodes.overview: A quick tempered opera singer is pacified by Hazel's boyfriend, Enzo.

episodes.name: Bonnie Boy
episodes.overview: The mayor appoints George to the committee investigating the sales of sweepstakes tickets and soon after, Hazel presents him with a present, a sweepstakes ticket.

episodes.name: Stop Rockin' Our Reception
episodes.overview: The television reception the Baxter's have been getting is unbearable and George accuses his neighbor's short-wave radio as the culprit.

episodes.name: What's Bugging Hazel?
episodes.overview: Gus, a friend of Hazel's, is caught with a bugging device while in a department store and is accused of being a spy for a rival store.

episodes.name: Hazel's Day in Court
episodes.overview: Hazel takes it upon herself to paint a crosswalk in the street in front of the Baxter home and quickly finds herslef in court.

episodes.name: Hazel's Inquisitive Mind
episodes.overview: The neighbor's maid becomes the object of Hazel's obsession when she tries to get the individual to join her club.  However, she is unaware that the maid is actually a Japanese houseboy.

episodes.name: George's Man Friday
episodes.overview: Hazel helps a gambler get a job as George's assistant.

episodes.name: The Investor
episodes.overview: A baker's wife has left him leaving him to run the store himself.  So in steps Hazel, who invests in the business after the baker refuses to sell the business.

episodes.name: Who's in Charge Here?
episodes.overview: George and Dorothy leave the country and Hazel and Harold moves in with George's brother, Steve, and his family.  Steve quickly finds his new housekeeper taking over the household.

episodes.name: Hazel's Second Week
episodes.overview: With Hazel taking care of the entire home, Barbara feels useless which prompts Hazel to decide to leave.

episodes.name: How to Lose 30 Pounds in 30 Minutes
episodes.overview: Wanting to lose 30lbs, Hazel joins a health spa and quickly finds losing any weight will be more than she bargained for.

episodes.name: How to Find Work Without Really Trying
